text: Young people are not at risk from Covid-19 at all.
There is no science or data to suggest that kids are at risk from COVID.
Children aren’t affected by Covid-19 and don’t transmit the virus.
To children and the vast majority of young and middle-aged adults and the vast majority of teachers, (the coronavirus) poses virtually zero threat.
80% of children are not being tested for coronavirus.
Children ages 5 to 9 are not affected by the coronavirus.
The seasonal cold and flu is actually more dangerous for kids than the Coronavirus and there is very low transmissibility from children to their families and communities.
Children can’t get the new coronavirus.
